DUNNING v. SMITH. (Circuit Court of Appeals, First Circuit. April 22, 1903.) No. 475. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the District of Massachusetts. E. S. Mansfield and George R. Swasey, for appellant. Jeremiah Smith, Jr., for appellee.

Before COLT and PUTNAM, Circuit Judges, and ALDRICH, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, without prejudice and without costs, as per stipulation on file.
